The paper presents a method for multi-object tracking in autonomous driving applications, which involves computer vision (CV) and robotics (RO) techniques. The method uses a probabilistic approach, which is related to machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI) fields. Finally, the paper focuses on the practical application of the method, which is related to systems and control (SY) field. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.RO, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.SY.
